com.helger.jcodemodel

Class JPrimitiveType

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.helger.jcodemodel.AbstractJType
      • com.helger.jcodemodel.JPrimitiveType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IJGenerable, IJOwned

    public class JPrimitiveType
extends AbstractJType
    Java built-in primitive types. Instances of this class can be obtained as constants of JCodeModel, such as JCodeModel.BOOLEAN.

      • wrap

        @Nonnull
public IJExpression wrap(@Nonnull
                        IJExpression aExpr)
        Wraps an expression of this type to the corresponding wrapper class. For example, if this class represents "float", this method will return the expression new Float(x) or Float.valueOf(x) for the parameter x.
        For void type it throws an IllegalStateException because this would lead to corrupt code!
        Parameters:
        aExpr - Expression to be wrapped
        Returns:
        The created expression. Never null
        See Also:
        useValueOf()

      • unwrap

        @Nonnull
public IJExpression unwrap(@Nonnull
                          IJExpression aExpr)
        Do the opposite of the wrap method. So for a Float object x it creates x.floatValue()
        For void type it throws an IllegalStateException because this would lead to corrupt code!
        Parameters:
        aExpr - Expression to be unwrapped
        Returns:
        The created primitive value expression. Never null

      • useValueOf

        public boolean useValueOf()
        Returns:
        true if valueOf should be used in wrap(IJExpression), false if new X(y) should be used there. Note: valueOf is faster in execution since it uses potentially built in caches of the objects.

      • useValueOf

        public void useValueOf(boolean bUseValueOf)
        Determine of valueOf should be used or not.
        Parameters:
        bUseValueOf - New value. true to enable usage of valueOf
